# PR Workflow Enforcement

- Use PR-first delivery for all implementation work:
  - create or switch to a task branch (`feature/<scope>`, `fix/<scope>`, `chore/<scope>`)
  - keep branches short-lived and single-slice
  - implement and test
  - push branch
  - open PR
  - verify publish/linkage (`scripts/pr/verify_publish.py`, `gh pr view`, `gh pr checks`)
  - run `/review-pr -> /prepare-pr -> /merge-pr`
  - finalize workflow (`main` sync + local/remote branch cleanup)
- Do not merge directly to `main` from a local branch.
- Do not skip maintainer workflow phases; each phase must produce artifacts:
  - `.local/review.md`
  - `.local/prep.md`
  - `.local/merge.md`
- Before merge, required gates must be green:
  - `python -m pytest -q`
  - `python scripts/pr/verify_publish.py --branch "$(git branch --show-current)"`
- Before merge, branch/PR linkage must be verifiably healthy:
  - current branch tracks `origin/<branch>`
  - remote branch exists (`git ls-remote --heads origin <branch>`)
  - PR head branch matches current branch (`gh pr view --json headRefName`)
- Use `git push --force-with-lease` only for intentional rewrites on branches you own.
- Do not use destructive git commands (`reset --hard`, forced history rewrites) unless explicitly requested.
- Stop and report instead of merging when any required artifact or gate result is missing.
- Stop and report instead of closing workflow when post-merge sync/cleanup is incomplete.
